thread.title_full: Baylor, Group of Five make moves in 1-128 Re-rank

author: azcentral.com
title: Baylor, Group of Five make moves in 1-128 Re-rank
text:
Familiar faces lead the USA TODAY Sports 1-128 Re-rank of FBS teams, though a new team tops the list: Baylor moves two spots to No. 1, exchanging places with fierce conference rival TCU.
Based on how each team has looked through the first half of the regular season — Baylor has looked untouchable, TCU has been unbeatable — it's very likely that these two Texas-based programs head into their November matchup with a No. 1 ranking on the line, let alone a spot in the College Football Playoff.
Follow the road to the 2015 College Football Playoff at The Football Four , our home to rate and debate the nation's best. Beyond the race for No. 1, the biggest story in this week's re-ranking can be found from members of the Group of Five. Four non-major programs sit inside the top 25, led by No. 12 Memphis, which soared into the championship mix after beating Mississippi. The Tigers are followed by No. 18 Temple, No. 22 Toledo and No. 23 Houston.
It's enough to offset Boise State's tumble. The Broncos were swamped by Utah State, 52-26, in a loss that should cost Bryan Harsin's team not just an access-bowl berth but a Mountain West Conference championship.
New to the top 25: Houston and Duke.
Out of the top 25: Boise State and UCLA.
